data.title: Emily Garrick - Women's Soccer 2021
data.meta_description: Women's Soccer 2021 - Emily Garrick: The Official Athletics Website for the Old Dominion Monarchs.
data.text:
2021: Appeared in 17 matches, making two game starts for the Monarchs ... Scored two goals on the season ... Attempted 10 shots during the season.

2020: Appeared in all 11 matches, making six starts ... Scored the game-winning goal against ECU … Dished out one assist versus WKU ... Compiled three total points (tied for fifth on the team) … Earned a Conference USA Commissioner’s Medal for work in the classroom … Named to Conference USA Honor Roll.

2019: Redshirted.

2018: Dean’s List, Conference USA Honor Roll and Commissioner’s Medal recipient … Compiled a perfect 4.0 term GPA … Appeared in 12 matches as a true freshman … Attempted five shots for the season.

High School: Attended Liberty High School ... Member of the National Honors Society ... Team Captain ... Honor Roll student ... Garnered All-County, All-Conference and All-State accolades ... Named to the ODP Regional and State Teams ... ENCL PPP Selection.

Personal/Additional: Daughter of Rob and Tina Garrick ... Has one sister, Hayley ... Camp counselor for younger children in high school ... Majoring in physical education.

“I chose ODU because I really liked the campus and the environment. I really connected with the coaches and wanted to be a part of the up and coming soccer program."
